cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with predicting object representations from visual brain regions. Additionally, the use of deep learning models and convolutional neural networks further supports this categorization. The paper also involves neural activity prediction, which could fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The use of end-to-end training and group convolutions suggests that the paper could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also fall under the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with predicting representations in the form of dissimilarity matrices.
